.TH "generic_pipe_buf_get" 9 "generic_pipe_buf_get" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
generic_pipe_buf_get \- get a reference to a &struct pipe_buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" generic_pipe_buf_get
.BI "(struct pipe_inode_info *pipe "  ","
.BI "struct pipe_buffer *buf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pipe" 12
the pipe that the buffer belongs to
.IP "buf" 12
the buffer to get a reference to
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function grabs an extra reference to \fIbuf\fP. It's used in
the \fBtee\fP system call, when we duplicate the buffers in one
pipe into another.
